page.title: 08Housing at Cutts End
page.content: The road out of Cumnor has a single row of houses along it. These were built in the 1930's-ribbon development being typical of that decade. In 1958, several houses were built in a space between the older houses. The garage mechanic who has lived at Cutts End for 16 years said that apart from extensions to the backs of some houses there has been no new building during that time. One family had great difficulty in obtaining {planning permission}to build along the line of the road. One resident feared that the Green Belt is slowly being eroded and that eventually urban development will spread out from Oxford and swamp Cumnor.
